WEBVTT

1
00:00:29.315 --> 00:00:30.316
Yes?

2
00:00:30.984 --> 00:00:34.320
Pierre, there's
an urgent call from France.


3
00:00:35.989 --> 00:00:37.991
After the concert.

4
00:00:41.911 --> 00:00:43.997
It's about your mother.

5
00:00:52.964 --> 00:00:54.007
Yes?

6
00:02:53.543 --> 00:02:55.962
Do you remember me?

7
00:02:57.213 --> 00:02:59.007
Fond de I'étang.

8
00:02:59.132 --> 00:03:01.593
"My father is coming for me
on Saturday."


9
00:03:03.344 --> 00:03:05.763
Pépinot.

10
00:03:05.805 --> 00:03:07.640
Of course.

11
00:03:09.058 --> 00:03:10.018
Pépinot.

12
00:03:11.102 --> 00:03:14.314
- How long has it been?
- About 50 years.


13
00:03:17.400 --> 00:03:18.902
Fond de I'étang.

14
00:03:22.196 --> 00:03:25.366
You're the little guy in the front row.

15
00:03:25.408 --> 00:03:27.577
And there you are.

16
00:03:27.702 --> 00:03:30.371
Do you remember the prefect's name?

17
00:03:30.455 --> 00:03:32.415
Clément Mathieu.

18
00:03:32.498 --> 00:03:34.042
Clément Mathieu.

19
00:03:36.044 --> 00:03:38.588
I wonder what happened to him.

20
00:03:40.715 --> 00:03:42.508
Open it.

21
00:03:47.305 --> 00:03:48.848
"Fond de I'étang.

22
00:03:48.932 --> 00:03:50.683
1949."

23
00:03:50.767 --> 00:03:54.646
Mathieu kept a journal
while he worked at Fond de I'étang.


24
00:03:54.687 --> 00:03:57.815
That's his story. Ours too.

25
00:03:59.108 --> 00:04:01.152
He wanted you to have it.

26
00:04:01.236 --> 00:04:05.406
I'd have preferred to deliver it
under different circumstances, but...


27
00:04:09.327 --> 00:04:11.704
"January 15, 1949.

28
00:04:12.830 --> 00:04:16.334
After failing for so long
in so many fields,


29
00:04:16.417 --> 00:04:19.629
I was sure the
worst was still to come."

30
00:04:20.755 --> 00:04:25.218
It was a boarding school where
troubled children were rehabilitated.


31
00:04:26.010 --> 00:04:28.596
That's what the advertisement said.

32
00:04:28.638 --> 00:04:30.723
Fond de I'étang.

33
00:04:30.807 --> 00:04:34.102
Even the name seemed
to fit me like a glove.


34
00:04:35.436 --> 00:04:36.437
Hello.

35
00:04:37.939 --> 00:04:39.899
You're all alone?

36
00:04:40.525 --> 00:04:42.318
What are you doing there?

37
00:04:43.403 --> 00:04:45.655
Waiting for Saturday.

38
00:04:45.697 --> 00:04:47.073
Why?

39
00:04:48.491 --> 00:04:50.952
My father is coming for me.

40
00:04:51.035 --> 00:04:53.162
But it's not Saturday.

41
00:04:53.246 --> 00:04:54.205
Pépinot.

42
00:04:55.540 --> 00:04:56.708
Pépinot.

43
00:04:57.709 --> 00:05:01.296
Hello. I'm Clément Mathieu,
the new prefect.


44
00:05:03.339 --> 00:05:05.341
Have you done this type of work before?

45
00:05:05.425 --> 00:05:07.427
I taught some classes in private school.

46
00:05:07.510 --> 00:05:09.512
- What did you teach?
- Music.


47
00:05:09.596 --> 00:05:14.142
You'll like Rachin, our headmaster.
He used to play the trumpet.


48
00:05:14.225 --> 00:05:15.810
- Hello, Pépinot.
- Hello.


49
00:05:15.893 --> 00:05:18.354
His daughters. 
He lives right there.

50
00:05:20.815 --> 00:05:23.818
- You haven't met Mr. Rachin?
- Not yet, no.


51
00:05:23.902 --> 00:05:26.571
- Mrs. Boissemand recommended me.
- Really?


52
00:05:26.654 --> 00:05:28.781
That was old Maxence.

53
00:05:28.865 --> 00:05:32.243
He told me on the spot
that he was the school watchman,


54
00:05:32.285 --> 00:05:35.830
as well as its nurse,
storekeeper and glazier.


55
00:05:38.541 --> 00:05:41.961
- What is he doing?
- Serving detention for Mr. Rachin.


56
00:05:42.545 --> 00:05:45.757
Fifteen days of community work.
In other words, school drudge.


57
00:05:45.840 --> 00:05:48.468
What kind of children are they, exactly?

58
00:05:48.551 --> 00:05:50.762
- No one told you?
- No.


59
00:05:52.597 --> 00:05:55.308
My infirmary. I'll show you
my vegetable garden later.


60
00:05:55.350 --> 00:05:56.935
I'd like that.

61
00:05:59.771 --> 00:06:02.523
- Damn it! What have they done now?
- I'll help you.


62
00:06:02.607 --> 00:06:04.609
Are you Clément Mathieu?

63
00:06:04.651 --> 00:06:06.486
The headmaster...

64
00:06:06.569 --> 00:06:09.239
Rachin, the school's headmaster.

65
00:06:09.280 --> 00:06:11.491
Headmaster, I'm sorry...

66
00:06:11.532 --> 00:06:14.160
- Yes, you're late.
- I had the wrong bus schedule.


67
00:06:14.244 --> 00:06:16.162
Punctuality is essential here.

68
00:06:16.246 --> 00:06:17.956
Very well.

69
00:06:18.039 --> 00:06:18.998
Headmaster.

70
00:06:20.124 --> 00:06:21.584
Very well, Headmaster.

71
00:06:21.626 --> 00:06:23.378
Come with me.

72
00:06:24.045 --> 00:06:27.298
First you should study
the school regulations,


73
00:06:27.340 --> 00:06:30.468
then you can supervise
the 4:00 study period before you...


74
00:06:33.763 --> 00:06:36.266
What are you doing? Answer me.

75
00:06:36.307 --> 00:06:38.184
- Take this.
- It's my eye.


76
00:06:38.268 --> 00:06:41.437
Another trap. You can appreciate
our boarders' finer instincts.


77
00:06:41.521 --> 00:06:43.606
Get him over there.

78
00:06:43.648 --> 00:06:45.400
I'm blinded.

79
00:06:45.483 --> 00:06:48.403
Don't make a fuss. Show me.

80
00:06:48.486 --> 00:06:50.613
It's not pretty.

81
00:06:50.655 --> 00:06:52.907
Ring the bell. 
School assembly.

82
00:06:52.991 --> 00:06:55.868
- We should call a doctor.
- Do you know how much they charge?


83
00:06:55.952 --> 00:06:58.413
What did I say? 
Ring the assembly.

84
00:06:58.454 --> 00:06:59.831
The bell?

85
00:06:59.914 --> 00:07:02.375
Next to the door,
right in front of you.


86
00:07:02.417 --> 00:07:03.418
All right.

87
00:07:06.588 --> 00:07:08.131
Assembly.

88
00:07:09.591 --> 00:07:11.134
Assembly.

89
00:07:12.468 --> 00:07:15.430
- Are they always like that?
- Keep ringing the bell.


90
00:07:25.106 --> 00:07:26.941
Two abreast.

91
00:07:30.945 --> 00:07:33.573
Everybody in the schoolyard.
Assembly.


92
00:07:37.243 --> 00:07:38.745
Hurry up.

93
00:07:39.537 --> 00:07:41.748
Move faster. Be silent.

94
00:07:42.999 --> 00:07:44.792
- Chrome Dome.
- Be silent.


95
00:07:46.419 --> 00:07:48.421
- Chrome Dome.
- Be silent.


96
00:07:50.465 --> 00:07:51.591
Be silent.

97
00:07:51.674 --> 00:07:53.676
- I didn't say anything.
- Be silent.


98
00:08:00.683 --> 00:08:02.852
I called this assembly

99
00:08:02.894 --> 00:08:06.648
because of a despicable attempt
against old Maxence.


100
00:08:06.731 --> 00:08:10.902
Under our action-reaction rule,
the culprit will be severely punished.


101
00:08:12.528 --> 00:08:15.657
I want the culprit's name
within the next three seconds,


102
00:08:15.740 --> 00:08:18.952
or it's six hours of lock-up
for each one of you.


103
00:08:19.035 --> 00:08:23.706
Effective until he's betrayed
or gives himself up.


104
00:08:23.790 --> 00:08:25.250
Is that clear?

105
00:08:25.333 --> 00:08:27.043
One...

106
00:08:27.126 --> 00:08:28.586
Two...

107
00:08:28.711 --> 00:08:30.421
Three.

108
00:08:30.505 --> 00:08:32.006
No volunteers?

109
00:08:32.090 --> 00:08:34.509
Of course. Come closer.

110
00:08:36.427 --> 00:08:38.304
- Mathieu.
- Me?


111
00:08:38.346 --> 00:08:40.306
Come closer.

112
00:08:40.348 --> 00:08:42.392
The school register, Mr. Chabert.

113
00:08:42.475 --> 00:08:43.977
Thank you.

114
00:08:44.060 --> 00:08:47.522
Mr. Mathieu, your new prefect,
has been spared your acquaintance.


115
00:08:47.605 --> 00:08:50.191
- Chrome Dome.
- Be silent.


116
00:08:50.233 --> 00:08:53.778
So he can choose
who goes first without bias.


117
00:08:57.907 --> 00:08:59.075
Be silent.

118
00:08:59.158 --> 00:09:01.286
Pick a name.

119
00:09:01.369 --> 00:09:03.079
At random?

120
00:09:05.248 --> 00:09:07.917
- A word of advice...
- Don't interfere. Go on.


121
00:09:11.546 --> 00:09:12.839
Boniface.

122
00:09:14.966 --> 00:09:17.093
Too bad. Chabert, get Boniface.

123
00:09:19.762 --> 00:09:22.265
- Sir, I didn't do anything.
- Shut up.


124
00:09:22.307 --> 00:09:25.184
- It's lousy, I didn't do anything.
- Watch your language.


125
00:09:25.268 --> 00:09:26.686
Move.

126
00:09:26.728 --> 00:09:29.063
- I won't go.
- I'll kick your backside for you.


127
00:09:29.147 --> 00:09:31.149
Be silent.

128
00:09:31.190 --> 00:09:33.693
Furthermore,
until I've found the culprit,


129
00:09:33.776 --> 00:09:36.905
there will be no recess
and no visitors.


130
00:09:37.030 --> 00:09:39.490
I advise you to give him up quickly.

131
00:09:39.574 --> 00:09:41.910
It's an encouragement to turn informer.

132
00:09:42.785 --> 00:09:45.747
You're full of noble illusions
like any new staff member.


133
00:09:45.788 --> 00:09:47.832
Come see me in eight days.

134
00:09:47.916 --> 00:09:51.210
You'll be replacing Mr. Régent.
He'll explain your duties.


135
00:09:55.590 --> 00:09:57.550
Clean sheets.

136
00:09:57.634 --> 00:09:58.968
Thank you.

137
00:10:01.179 --> 00:10:03.181
Why are you leaving?

138
00:10:04.766 --> 00:10:07.060
Ten stitches.

139
00:10:07.143 --> 00:10:09.562
Cut with scissors.

140
00:10:09.646 --> 00:10:12.523
Just for confiscating
Mouton's cigarettes.


141
00:10:12.607 --> 00:10:15.401
- Mouton?
- The boy's name is Mouton.


142
00:10:17.487 --> 00:10:19.614
And Mouton's still here?

143
00:10:22.408 --> 00:10:25.453
By the way, Le Querrec
booby-trapped Maxence's door.


144
00:10:25.495 --> 00:10:28.498
I heard him talking about it
in the corridor.


145
00:10:28.581 --> 00:10:31.501
- And you didn't say anything?
- I didn't want to miss the bus.


146
00:10:32.502 --> 00:10:35.213
Old Maxence punished him
for breaking some glass panes.


147
00:10:35.296 --> 00:10:37.590
Simple revenge. 
That's just his style.

148
00:10:38.591 --> 00:10:39.926
Le Querrec.

149
00:10:41.427 --> 00:10:43.846
Don't forget that name: Le Querrec.

150
00:10:43.930 --> 00:10:45.431
- Morhange too.
- Yes.


151
00:10:45.515 --> 00:10:48.518
Morhange doesn't talk much,
but keep an eye on him.


152
00:10:48.601 --> 00:10:51.604
Looks like an angel,
acts like the devil.


153
00:10:51.688 --> 00:10:53.731
Action-reaction.

154
00:10:53.815 --> 00:10:55.817
That's all they understand.

155
00:10:59.320 --> 00:11:01.322
They're all yours.

156
00:11:03.074 --> 00:11:05.243
- Good luck.
- Thank you.


157
00:11:13.167 --> 00:11:14.877
Our benefactresses.

158
00:11:15.003 --> 00:11:16.921
The timetable's over there.

159
00:11:17.046 --> 00:11:19.507
Classes were shared
between the headmaster,


160
00:11:19.591 --> 00:11:21.593
who taught French and History,

161
00:11:21.676 --> 00:11:25.305
and Mr. Langlois,
who taught every other subject.


162
00:11:25.388 --> 00:11:27.640
Mr. Langlois, here's the new prefect.

163
00:11:27.724 --> 00:11:29.517
Clément Mathieu.

164
00:11:29.601 --> 00:11:33.271
- A prefect at your age?
- Yes, but I used to teach.


165
00:11:33.396 --> 00:11:35.732
Very well then.

166
00:11:39.777 --> 00:11:42.196
And he's the funny one.

167
00:11:42.238 --> 00:11:46.242
Take your study period. You're late.
No need to show you the way.


168
00:12:09.682 --> 00:12:11.601
Watch out. Chrome Dome's coming.

169
00:12:19.901 --> 00:12:21.819
Gentlemen.

170
00:12:26.908 --> 00:12:28.868
No smoking during class.

171
00:12:30.328 --> 00:12:33.039
The rules apply to everyone.
Even you, sir.


172
00:12:37.126 --> 00:12:39.754
Give it back.

173
00:12:39.837 --> 00:12:41.297
Be quiet.

174
00:12:41.381 --> 00:12:42.966
Give it back.

175
00:12:43.925 --> 00:12:46.094
Be silent.

176
00:12:46.135 --> 00:12:47.637
Give it back.

177
00:12:51.057 --> 00:12:54.143
An auspicious beginning.
Congratulations, Mathieu.


178
00:12:54.227 --> 00:12:55.812
Sit.

179
00:12:58.565 --> 00:12:59.857
Of course.

180
00:12:59.899 --> 00:13:02.735
You again.

181
00:13:02.819 --> 00:13:06.072
What did he do?

182
00:13:06.197 --> 00:13:07.657
Nothing, Headmaster.

183
00:13:08.741 --> 00:13:12.078
What do you mean, "nothing?"
You were about to punish him.


184
00:13:12.161 --> 00:13:14.664
I asked him to go to the blackboard

185
00:13:14.747 --> 00:13:17.083
and I was just telling them
to be silent.


186
00:13:17.166 --> 00:13:19.919
Not a minute too soon.

187
00:13:20.878 --> 00:13:22.880
Don't make me come back.

188
00:13:29.262 --> 00:13:31.806
Stand in the corner.

189
00:13:33.016 --> 00:13:34.976
Very well.

190
00:13:35.018 --> 00:13:40.064
Now that you've come to know me,
we need to set things straight.


191
00:13:40.148 --> 00:13:43.234
Right now,
one of your classmates is in lock-up.


192
00:13:43.318 --> 00:13:45.278
For no good reason.

193
00:13:45.361 --> 00:13:48.656
I may not look like much
but I'm no fool.


194
00:13:48.740 --> 00:13:50.700
I know who did it.

195
00:13:50.783 --> 00:13:53.870
He has 15 seconds to give himself up.

196
00:13:57.040 --> 00:13:58.917
I'm waiting.

197
00:14:00.668 --> 00:14:03.630
You'll regret it. 
Five seconds left.

198
00:14:05.632 --> 00:14:07.842
Too late.

199
00:14:08.718 --> 00:14:10.178
Le Querrec.

200
00:14:11.262 --> 00:14:12.805
Who is Le Querrec?

201
00:14:13.765 --> 00:14:15.934
I am, sir.

202
00:14:17.143 --> 00:14:18.937
What a surprise.

203
00:14:19.437 --> 00:14:22.857
- You hurt Mr. Maxence.
- No, sir. I didn't do it.


204
00:14:22.941 --> 00:14:25.652
- That wasn't a question.
- I didn't do anything.


205
00:14:25.693 --> 00:14:28.863
Between the two of us, I wonder
who the headmaster will believe.


206
00:14:28.947 --> 00:14:34.327
I need someone dependable
to keep an eye on things while I'm gone.


207
00:14:34.369 --> 00:14:38.456
According to my sixth sense,
that dependable student must be...


208
00:14:38.539 --> 00:14:40.333
...Mr. Morhange.

209
00:14:41.960 --> 00:14:45.380
Come on, come on.
Who is Mr. Morhange?


210
00:14:46.506 --> 00:14:48.299
That's me, sir.

211
00:14:55.431 --> 00:14:58.226
So you're the angel.

212
00:14:59.227 --> 00:15:03.147
Go down. You'll supervise
the class while I'm gone.


213
00:15:03.231 --> 00:15:04.983
Go on.

214
00:15:05.066 --> 00:15:09.487
Nice. You could pull out
your shirt a bit more.


215
00:15:09.571 --> 00:15:13.825
I'm told the rebellious have
strong leadership skills. Prove it.


216
00:15:14.826 --> 00:15:17.579
Come to the headmaster's office.

217
00:15:19.956 --> 00:15:22.417
- Have mercy, sir.
- Mercy?


218
00:15:22.500 --> 00:15:26.212
What about the boy who's taken
your place? And old Maxence?


219
00:15:26.254 --> 00:15:28.756
I didn't want to hurt him.
It was just a joke.


220
00:15:28.840 --> 00:15:30.508
A joke?

221
00:15:30.592 --> 00:15:35.638
...a little stint in lock-up.
I've had enough of you.


222
00:15:35.722 --> 00:15:39.225
But first, I'm going to give you
the flogging of your life.


223
00:15:42.312 --> 00:15:44.397
- Who is it?
- Leclerc.


224
00:15:44.439 --> 00:15:48.943
He's tried to run away three times.
He's taking him to lock-up.


225
00:15:48.985 --> 00:15:51.279
- So you won't be alone.
- Don't.


226
00:15:54.657 --> 00:15:58.286
Maybe we can come to an agreement.

227
00:15:58.369 --> 00:16:00.872
You hurt Mr. Maxence. Badly.

228
00:16:00.955 --> 00:16:04.417
I won't take you to the headmaster
but I have to punish you.


229
00:16:05.501 --> 00:16:10.340
Instead of fooling around during recess,
you'll work in the infirmary.


230
00:16:10.381 --> 00:16:12.926
You'll be old Maxence's nurse.

231
00:16:12.967 --> 00:16:15.678
You'll look after him until he's cured.

232
00:16:15.762 --> 00:16:17.221
All right?

233
00:16:36.032 --> 00:16:37.909
Not bad.

234
00:16:37.992 --> 00:16:39.786
What do you think?

235
00:16:39.869 --> 00:16:43.373
But I can do better. Give me the chalk.
Stand in profile.


236
00:16:43.498 --> 00:16:45.166
Profile.

237
00:16:58.972 --> 00:17:01.516
Let's see a smile for a change.

238
00:17:01.599 --> 00:17:04.519
You can look now.

239
00:17:04.561 --> 00:17:08.064
I almost forgot...
Some color would be nice.


240
00:17:11.609 --> 00:17:14.112
Much better. Get back to your seat.

241
00:17:15.822 --> 00:17:17.740
Very well.

242
00:17:17.824 --> 00:17:22.495
I want to get to know you,
so you're going to write your name,


243
00:17:22.579 --> 00:17:26.207
your age and your dream job
on a piece of paper.


244
00:17:32.505 --> 00:17:36.301
I was astonished when
they all did as they were told.


245
00:17:40.471 --> 00:17:43.391
All except one.

246
00:17:47.228 --> 00:17:49.230
You're not writing?

247
00:17:51.774 --> 00:17:54.777
How long have you been here?

248
00:17:54.819 --> 00:17:57.363
A long time?

249
00:17:57.405 --> 00:17:59.532
I don't know.

250
00:18:01.326 --> 00:18:03.411
Write, little fellow.

251
00:18:19.385 --> 00:18:22.013
An exhausting first day.

252
00:18:22.055 --> 00:18:25.308
I forgot why I came here
in the first place.


253
00:18:25.350 --> 00:18:29.646
Rachin scares me, the building
scares me, even the children scare me.


254
00:18:29.687 --> 00:18:34.067
I keep expecting them
to slip into my recess and murder me.


255
00:18:34.108 --> 00:18:35.610
My blanket.

256
00:18:36.861 --> 00:18:39.322
- Got a cigarette?
- Shut up.


257
00:18:39.405 --> 00:18:40.907
Go to bed.

258
00:18:56.464 --> 00:18:59.801
I read the assignments again.

259
00:18:59.884 --> 00:19:02.387
They all had fabulous dreams.

260
00:19:02.470 --> 00:19:05.848
Two firemen, three cowboys,
one tiger tamer, one fighter pilot,


261
00:19:05.932 --> 00:19:10.728
two spies, a general under Napoleon,
one balloonist, three legionaries...


262
00:19:11.729 --> 00:19:14.190
Not one school prefect.

263
00:19:15.900 --> 00:19:19.070
It was nice of you
to volunteer to be my nurse.


264
00:19:19.153 --> 00:19:24.534
Doctor, the new prefect asked
for a volunteer to take care of me.


265
00:19:24.576 --> 00:19:27.537
And he raised his hand right away.

266
00:19:27.579 --> 00:19:30.123
Proof that
we should believe in miracles.


267
00:19:30.164 --> 00:19:32.166
Come in.

268
00:19:32.250 --> 00:19:34.961
Mr. Mathieu, the new prefect.

269
00:19:36.838 --> 00:19:38.047
So?

270
00:19:38.131 --> 00:19:41.259
It's pretty bad, Maxence.

271
00:19:41.342 --> 00:19:44.345
If they've started attacking you,
they're beyond help.


272
00:19:44.429 --> 00:19:47.473
You're so patient with them.

273
00:19:47.557 --> 00:19:51.227
I've got a thick skull.
You shouldn't be feeling sorry for me.


274
00:19:51.311 --> 00:19:54.939
I feel sorry for those poor kids.
Don't forget one of them is dead.


275
00:19:55.023 --> 00:19:56.441
Dead?

276
00:19:56.524 --> 00:19:59.277
His name was Mouton.
He jumped off the roof.


277
00:19:59.402 --> 00:20:01.613
Good thing he was an orphan.

278
00:20:01.696 --> 00:20:04.866
Look at him. Everyone says
he's a lost cause. It's not true.


279
00:20:04.949 --> 00:20:08.411
He's a good boy.
You just have to know him.


280
00:20:08.494 --> 00:20:10.663
Old Maxence is a nice guy.

281
00:20:12.248 --> 00:20:15.960
I'm talking to you, Le Querrec.
Don't you think he's nice?


282
00:20:17.295 --> 00:20:19.297
No?

283
00:20:19.380 --> 00:20:20.381
Yes.

284
00:20:20.465 --> 00:20:22.967
- I didn't hear you.
- Leave him alone. He's shy.


285
00:20:23.051 --> 00:20:24.761
Like me.

286
00:20:26.387 --> 00:20:28.598
One, two, three, four...

287
00:20:31.059 --> 00:20:33.019
Faster.

288
00:20:35.521 --> 00:20:36.606
Yes?

289
00:20:36.689 --> 00:20:39.317
- I'd like a word, Headmaster.
- Leaving us so soon?


290
00:20:39.400 --> 00:20:42.862
- No, I'd like to try something.
- You don't say.


291
00:20:42.946 --> 00:20:46.074
About the accident.

292
00:20:46.157 --> 00:20:48.534
- That was no accident.
- Quite.


293
00:20:48.576 --> 00:20:50.620
I need three things from you.

294
00:20:50.703 --> 00:20:53.831
- Is that all?
- One, cancel the group punishment,


295
00:20:53.915 --> 00:20:59.921
two, let me deal with the culprit,
and three, don't ask me for his name.


296
00:21:00.046 --> 00:21:02.257
You'd have to know it first.

297
00:21:02.340 --> 00:21:03.800
Naturally.

298
00:21:03.883 --> 00:21:08.054
Your arrogance astounds me.
Do you really think you'll find him?


299
00:21:08.137 --> 00:21:12.058
Very well. If you succeed,
I'll cancel the group punishment.


300
00:21:12.141 --> 00:21:15.728
But you'll never get the culprit
or I'm the biggest fool in nature.


301
00:21:17.480 --> 00:21:20.233
I know who did it, Headmaster.

302
00:21:21.526 --> 00:21:23.736
Congratulations.

303
00:21:23.778 --> 00:21:26.322
Who is it?

304
00:21:26.406 --> 00:21:28.658
You said I wouldn't have to tell you.

305
00:21:30.076 --> 00:21:32.912
Fine. Very well then.

306
00:21:32.954 --> 00:21:35.039
But I don't like your manners.

307
00:21:35.123 --> 00:21:38.001
You'd better make sure
your students behave.


308
00:21:38.042 --> 00:21:41.713
- I've already got them under control.
- That's what you think.


309
00:21:41.754 --> 00:21:44.549
One, two, three, four... Go on.

310
00:21:45.758 --> 00:21:47.010
Faster.

311
00:22:01.065 --> 00:22:04.903
- There's no pictures of naked women.
- I never said there were naked women.


312
00:22:04.944 --> 00:22:06.946
What does yours say?

313
00:22:07.030 --> 00:22:10.825
"Ave Maria for soprano
by Clément Mathieu."


314
00:22:10.909 --> 00:22:14.495
I've got, "String quartet...

315
00:22:14.537 --> 00:22:17.707
...by Clément Mathieu."
- Looks like music.


316
00:22:17.790 --> 00:22:20.293
- What do you know about it?
- Maybe it's Morse.


317
00:22:20.376 --> 00:22:22.837
- Or some secret code.
- Maybe he's no prefect.


318
00:22:22.879 --> 00:22:25.340
Maybe he's an undercover spy.

319
00:22:25.423 --> 00:22:26.716
Chrome Dome.

320
00:22:37.518 --> 00:22:39.479
Give it back to me.

321
00:22:39.604 --> 00:22:42.190
- What is it, sir?
- None of your business.


322
00:22:42.273 --> 00:22:45.193
Is there a problem, Mathieu?

323
00:22:45.276 --> 00:22:47.445
No problem.

324
00:22:47.487 --> 00:22:49.489
It's just music.

325
00:22:49.572 --> 00:22:51.282
What for?

326
00:22:52.242 --> 00:22:53.701
A chorus.

327
00:22:54.744 --> 00:22:56.746
In the water closets?

328
00:22:58.331 --> 00:23:00.792
Clear out, chorus.

329
00:23:06.339 --> 00:23:08.925
- Not here, Mathieu.
- What?


330
00:23:09.008 --> 00:23:11.719
- Don't play the idiot.
- You're not suggesting...?


331
00:23:11.761 --> 00:23:13.846
I won't say anything this time.

332
00:23:14.931 --> 00:23:18.351
- You really see evil everywhere.
- In here? Yes.


333
00:23:25.775 --> 00:23:28.194
Baldy, you are through

334
00:23:28.236 --> 00:23:31.072
The rules won't be made by you

335
00:23:31.155 --> 00:23:33.658
Baldy, you are through

336
00:23:33.741 --> 00:23:36.119
The rules won't be made by you

337
00:23:52.427 --> 00:23:54.596
The rules won't be made by you

338
00:23:54.679 --> 00:23:57.015
Chickening out, guys?

339
00:23:58.892 --> 00:24:01.936
- You're Corbin.
- Yes, sir, but I didn't do anything.


340
00:24:02.020 --> 00:24:04.147
- You were singing.
- No, sir. I swear.


341
00:24:04.272 --> 00:24:08.318
You were singing. Badly.
And you couldn't even tell.


342
00:24:08.359 --> 00:24:09.861
Go on. Sing.

343
00:24:09.903 --> 00:24:12.488
I'm listening.

344
00:24:12.530 --> 00:24:15.950
Would you prefer to sing
for the headmaster? Go on.


345
00:24:16.034 --> 00:24:18.536
Chrome Dome
Prepare to meet your doom


346
00:24:19.621 --> 00:24:21.664
Chrome Dome
Prepare to meet your doom


347
00:24:21.706 --> 00:24:24.042
You're not the boss of us

348
00:24:24.125 --> 00:24:26.544
You're not the boss of us

349
00:24:26.586 --> 00:24:28.963
No one ever told you
you couldn't sing?


350
00:24:29.047 --> 00:24:32.300
Sir? Is that really music
in your satchel?


351
00:24:32.383 --> 00:24:34.469
Mind your own business.

352
00:24:36.179 --> 00:24:40.350
By the way, if I ever catch
one of you messing with my things...


353
00:24:41.893 --> 00:24:44.187
...he'll be very sorry.

354
00:24:44.229 --> 00:24:46.981
Now be quiet.
Time to go to bed. Hurry up.


355
00:24:47.065 --> 00:24:48.566
It's over.

356
00:25:03.665 --> 00:25:05.667
Go to sleep.

357
00:25:24.102 --> 00:25:27.188
I couldn't get their ditty
out of my head.


358
00:25:27.272 --> 00:25:30.608
They're not very good at it,
but they are singing.


359
00:25:30.692 --> 00:25:33.570
I even spotted a few good voices.

360
00:25:34.737 --> 00:25:38.324
Are those kids really a lost cause?

361
00:25:38.408 --> 00:25:41.452
And I had sworn never
to touch my music again.


362
00:25:43.204 --> 00:25:45.081
Never say never.

363
00:25:46.082 --> 00:25:48.960
Nothing is ever truly lost.

364
00:25:57.385 --> 00:25:59.178
January 23rd.

365
00:25:59.262 --> 00:26:03.349
One week after his accident, old Maxence
suddenly took a turn for the worse.


366
00:26:03.433 --> 00:26:06.144
The doctor sent him to the hospital.

367
00:26:11.316 --> 00:26:13.860
Is he going to die?

368
00:26:14.861 --> 00:26:17.196
No, we'll save him.

369
00:26:19.490 --> 00:26:22.035
The very same day,
Pépinot got into trouble.


370
00:26:22.076 --> 00:26:25.121
Mr. Pépinot, you're a dunce.

371
00:26:25.204 --> 00:26:30.043
Final question. The last one.
How did Marshal Ney die?


372
00:26:38.968 --> 00:26:40.720
I'm waiting.

373
00:26:51.439 --> 00:26:52.732
Hunting?

374
00:26:54.776 --> 00:26:55.735
Zero.

375
00:26:55.818 --> 00:26:59.322
One hundred lines by tomorrow:
"Marshal Ney was shot."


376
00:27:00.323 --> 00:27:01.866
Get out.

377
00:27:10.208 --> 00:27:12.502
Boniface. Come here, boy.

378
00:27:16.089 --> 00:27:18.758
Here, as a reward for your essay.

379
00:27:18.800 --> 00:27:21.177
Give it to Mrs. Marie
and you'll get a cookie.


380
00:27:21.261 --> 00:27:24.264
You knew Ney had been shot, eh?

381
00:27:24.347 --> 00:27:26.391
Of course, sir. 
Just like Napoleon.

382
00:27:28.351 --> 00:27:29.769
Get out.

383
00:27:30.770 --> 00:27:33.565
Hold on, Mr. Morhange.

384
00:27:33.648 --> 00:27:35.692
I saw you taking notes during class.

385
00:27:35.733 --> 00:27:40.572
This is a rare occurrence indeed.
Bring me your notebook.


386
00:27:57.088 --> 00:27:58.214
Charming.

387
00:28:02.677 --> 00:28:06.014
Read it.
Admire the spelling.


388
00:28:11.895 --> 00:28:15.356
"Mr. Rachin eats shit by the bushel."

389
00:28:15.440 --> 00:28:17.025
He wrote "Mr.?"

390
00:28:18.151 --> 00:28:19.485
No.

391
00:28:19.569 --> 00:28:22.530
Action-reaction, Mr. Mathieu.

392
00:28:22.614 --> 00:28:24.073
Lock-up.

393
00:28:29.787 --> 00:28:31.247
Come on.

394
00:28:53.144 --> 00:28:56.522
- Gentlemen, enjoy your meal.
- Thank you.


395
00:28:57.649 --> 00:28:59.734
Are you hungry, Pépinot?

396
00:29:05.365 --> 00:29:07.617
Now you can eat.

397
00:29:07.700 --> 00:29:09.118
Pépinot?

398
00:29:09.160 --> 00:29:10.578
He's an orphan.

399
00:29:10.620 --> 00:29:12.747
His parents died
during the Occupation.


400
00:29:13.790 --> 00:29:15.875
- How did they die?
- I don't know.


401
00:29:15.917 --> 00:29:19.045
The kid thinks his father
will come for him on a Saturday.


402
00:29:20.964 --> 00:29:23.049
No one ever comes on Saturday.

403
00:29:23.132 --> 00:29:26.177
So we tell him he'll come
next Saturday, and so on.


404
00:29:26.261 --> 00:29:28.346
It'd be easier to tell him the truth.

405
00:29:28.388 --> 00:29:31.599
We must have told him 100 times.
He won't listen.


406
00:29:31.683 --> 00:29:36.521
Now we let him wait by the gate.
Let him enjoy himself.


407
00:29:38.064 --> 00:29:39.774
Be quiet!

408
00:29:41.442 --> 00:29:44.487
Did you see that? 
Action-reaction.

409
00:29:44.571 --> 00:29:46.114
Meaning?

410
00:29:46.197 --> 00:29:47.699
Action.

411
00:29:47.740 --> 00:29:49.367
Reaction.

412
00:29:49.450 --> 00:29:52.120
There's a visitor for young Morhange.

413
00:29:52.203 --> 00:29:54.080
Morhange is in lock-up.

414
00:29:54.205 --> 00:29:56.666
No visitors for the punished.
You know the rules.


415
00:29:56.749 --> 00:29:59.711
Go tell his visitor then.

416
00:30:25.153 --> 00:30:26.988
Good day, madame.

417
00:30:27.071 --> 00:30:28.531
Good day.

418
00:30:28.573 --> 00:30:30.700
I'm the new prefect.

419
00:30:31.451 --> 00:30:33.411
I'm Pierre Morhange's mother.

420
00:30:33.494 --> 00:30:35.455
Clément Mathieu.

421
00:30:35.496 --> 00:30:39.584
I know this isn't the right day,
but it's the only time I could...


422
00:30:39.667 --> 00:30:43.087
- No, that's not the problem.
- Has he been punished again?


423
00:30:43.212 --> 00:30:45.715
No, nothing like that...

424
00:30:45.798 --> 00:30:48.176
...but he's not here.

425
00:30:48.259 --> 00:30:50.386
What do you mean?

426
00:30:50.470 --> 00:30:53.848
They took him to the dentist.
He had a toothache.


427
00:30:53.932 --> 00:30:55.558
A toothache?

428
00:30:55.642 --> 00:30:59.354
Yes, but nothing serious.
He'll be back tonight.


429
00:31:00.521 --> 00:31:03.816
I can't wait.
I'm going back to work at 5.


430
00:31:04.859 --> 00:31:06.861
Can I leave something for him?

431
00:31:06.945 --> 00:31:08.988
Of course.

432
00:31:12.283 --> 00:31:16.162
Her name is Violette.
Violette Morhange.


433
00:31:16.204 --> 00:31:19.207
A single mother at her wits' end
about her son,


434
00:31:19.290 --> 00:31:24.462
a thieving introvert expelled from
school because he kept running away.


435
00:31:24.504 --> 00:31:28.675
When Pierre was sent to Fond de
I'étang against his mother's wishes,


436
00:31:28.758 --> 00:31:33.680
she told the judge, "At least
he'll get a hot meal twice a day."


437
00:31:35.932 --> 00:31:38.309
January 30th. The experience begins.

438
00:31:38.601 --> 00:31:41.688
In Brittany, the hats are...

439
00:31:42.188 --> 00:31:45.567
In Brittany, the hats are round

440
00:31:45.650 --> 00:31:48.945
That's why I'm Brittany bound

441
00:31:48.987 --> 00:31:52.115
Soprano. Go left.

442
00:31:52.156 --> 00:31:53.866
Leclerc.

443
00:31:56.244 --> 00:32:01.040
He is born, the Holy Child
Let us greet His coming


444
00:32:01.124 --> 00:32:03.585
Almost in tune.
Alto, go left.


445
00:32:04.460 --> 00:32:06.004
Delaire.

446
00:32:08.339 --> 00:32:11.843
Three miles on foot
What does it use?


447
00:32:11.968 --> 00:32:14.679
Three miles on foot
eats up your shoes


448
00:32:14.762 --> 00:32:16.264
Do it again.

449
00:32:16.347 --> 00:32:19.475
Four miles on foot
What does it use?


450
00:32:19.559 --> 00:32:22.020
Four miles on foot
eats up your shoes


451
00:32:22.145 --> 00:32:25.523
I was right. Bass, go right.

452
00:32:25.565 --> 00:32:27.066
Ricoeur.

453
00:32:29.569 --> 00:32:33.531
I've got tobacco in my pouch

454
00:32:33.573 --> 00:32:35.575
I'll give it away, not today

455
00:32:35.658 --> 00:32:38.661
Smoking is strictly forbidden.
Alto, left.


456
00:32:39.662 --> 00:32:41.247
Illouz.

457
00:32:44.459 --> 00:32:47.378
Love is a gypsy child

458
00:32:47.462 --> 00:32:50.423
That obeys no one's laws

459
00:32:50.465 --> 00:32:53.843
Soprano, of course. Left.

460
00:32:53.927 --> 00:32:56.137
Very well. Pépinot.

461
00:32:59.974 --> 00:33:01.935
I don't know any songs.

462
00:33:02.018 --> 00:33:04.354
That's fine. I'll teach you some.

463
00:33:05.813 --> 00:33:10.068
In the meantime,
you can be Assistant Chorus Master.


464
00:33:12.403 --> 00:33:13.696
Over there.

465
00:33:16.699 --> 00:33:19.410
Boniface.

466
00:33:21.204 --> 00:33:24.374
Marshal Pétain, here we are

467
00:33:24.457 --> 00:33:27.835
- Who taught you that?
- My grandfather.


468
00:33:27.877 --> 00:33:30.296
A little old-fashioned. Left.

469
00:33:31.214 --> 00:33:32.382
Clément.

470
00:33:34.842 --> 00:33:38.471
Citizens to arms
Display your charms


471
00:33:38.555 --> 00:33:40.014
Enough. Right.

472
00:33:40.056 --> 00:33:42.183
My camp counselor's a jerk

473
00:33:42.225 --> 00:33:45.061
He doesn't do any work

474
00:33:45.103 --> 00:33:46.187
Go left.

475
00:33:46.229 --> 00:33:49.357
Cuckoo, booboo
Cuckoo, booboo


476
00:33:52.735 --> 00:33:54.153
Good. Alto.

477
00:34:05.123 --> 00:34:07.250
Strong beat.

478
00:34:07.333 --> 00:34:09.085
Strong beat.

479
00:34:22.640 --> 00:34:24.559
Show me, Corbin.

480
00:34:32.066 --> 00:34:35.153
Sorry, there's no such note.
Come here.


481
00:34:36.237 --> 00:34:38.656
Mr. Pépinot, hand me the score.

482
00:34:39.157 --> 00:34:41.993
Thank you. Open your hands.

483
00:34:42.076 --> 00:34:44.662
Hold them like this.

484
00:34:44.746 --> 00:34:46.706
Good. You can be our lectern.

485
00:34:48.708 --> 00:34:50.418
Baton, Mr. Pépinot.

486
00:34:51.461 --> 00:34:53.129
Thank you.

487
00:34:55.173 --> 00:34:57.091
Get ready. On three...

488
00:35:04.766 --> 00:35:05.725
Again.

489
00:35:09.979 --> 00:35:11.522
That's it.

490
00:35:11.606 --> 00:35:13.316
One, two, three, four.

491
00:35:13.399 --> 00:35:16.527
Le Querrec's on bread and water...

492
00:35:16.653 --> 00:35:19.864
Every night, I make them practice
a simple tune of my own.


493
00:35:19.948 --> 00:35:23.076
Carpentier has lost his way

494
00:35:23.117 --> 00:35:26.955
Fond de I'Etang is where
we're stuck, just our luck


495
00:35:26.996 --> 00:35:30.750
Fond de I'Etang is where we'll be
for all eternity


496
00:35:39.592 --> 00:35:41.469
Not bad.

497
00:35:41.511 --> 00:35:44.514
It wasn't Mozart,
but I had their attention now.


498
00:35:44.597 --> 00:35:48.351
From now on, I would need
the support of my superiors.


499
00:35:48.393 --> 00:35:50.895
What?

500
00:35:50.979 --> 00:35:52.897
A chorus?

501
00:35:52.981 --> 00:35:54.190
Yes.

502
00:35:54.315 --> 00:35:58.236
My poor man, you've completely lost it.

503
00:35:58.278 --> 00:36:02.073
A chorus. You won't get a single note
from them or I'm the biggest fool...


504
00:36:02.115 --> 00:36:04.784
Please, Headmaster,
don't finish your sentence.


505
00:36:04.826 --> 00:36:06.578
Why not?

506
00:36:06.661 --> 00:36:08.538
They're singing already.

507
00:36:08.663 --> 00:36:10.123
Really?

508
00:36:10.164 --> 00:36:11.624
Just a few notes.

509
00:36:11.708 --> 00:36:15.295
Why ask my permission
if you're already doing it?


510
00:36:15.378 --> 00:36:17.380
I don't like your manners.

511
00:36:17.463 --> 00:36:20.091
- Headmaster...
- You're annoying me.


512
00:36:20.174 --> 00:36:22.302
I have other things on my mind.

