1023
01:17:53.710 --> 01:17:56.004
Is so sweet

1024
01:17:56.045 --> 01:18:00.717
Is there anything more beautiful

1025
01:18:00.800 --> 01:18:06.431
Than a dream?

1026
01:18:06.514 --> 01:18:11.269
Is there any truth

1027
01:18:11.352 --> 01:18:14.272
Sweeter

1028
01:18:14.355 --> 01:18:20.361
Than hope?

1029
01:18:35.835 --> 01:18:39.130
Morhange's eyes followed my tempo,

1030
01:18:39.172 --> 01:18:41.841
and in them,
I suddenly read many things:


1031
01:18:41.925 --> 01:18:44.802
pride and
the joy of my forgiveness,


1032
01:18:44.886 --> 01:18:47.805
but also something quite new to him.

1033
01:18:47.889 --> 01:18:49.766
A feeling of gratitude.

1034
01:18:51.935 --> 01:18:54.270
First day of summer.

1035
01:18:54.354 --> 01:18:57.148
Our chorus has a new member.

1036
01:19:01.653 --> 01:19:05.156
I'm sorry, I missed the reprise.
My fault. Go on.


1037
01:19:05.240 --> 01:19:06.991
All right. Again.

1038
01:19:32.183 --> 01:19:35.853
In their eyes,
I can see the desire to flee,


1039
01:19:35.937 --> 01:19:38.481
to build a hut
way up in the sky.

1040
01:19:38.565 --> 01:19:41.025
This fine weather makes them sad.

1041
01:20:00.879 --> 01:20:03.631
You have to see this. 
It's important.

1042
01:20:06.843 --> 01:20:09.470
While I was cleaning graffiti
off the toilet walls,


1043
01:20:09.554 --> 01:20:12.015
I lifted a stone and found this.

1044
01:20:12.724 --> 01:20:15.018
- That's Corbin's harmonica.
- And that.


1045
01:20:15.101 --> 01:20:17.228
It's 200,000 or more.

1046
01:20:26.905 --> 01:20:29.157
No one knew about your hideaway.

1047
01:20:30.700 --> 01:20:33.786
So don't tell me
it was there by chance.


1048
01:20:33.828 --> 01:20:36.873
You know they expelled Mondain
because of the theft.


1049
01:20:36.956 --> 01:20:38.917
I didn't know.

1050
01:20:39.000 --> 01:20:42.086
That's true. You didn't know.

1051
01:20:42.128 --> 01:20:44.130
Now you know.

1052
01:20:44.172 --> 01:20:46.674
Why? What did you
want to do with it?

1053
01:20:48.134 --> 01:20:50.720
If I tell you,
will you tell anyone else?


1054
01:20:50.803 --> 01:20:52.430
No one.

1055
01:20:52.472 --> 01:20:54.474
I swear.

1056
01:20:56.476 --> 01:20:58.561
I wanted to buy...

1057
01:20:58.645 --> 01:21:00.563
To buy what?

1058
01:21:01.397 --> 01:21:03.524
A hot air balloon.

1059
01:21:04.943 --> 01:21:07.987
I don't know who took it,
but it proves Mondain's innocence.


1060
01:21:08.071 --> 01:21:10.532
He'd never have left without the money.

1061
01:21:10.573 --> 01:21:13.034
I'll investigate when I come back.

1062
01:21:13.117 --> 01:21:15.161
But don't worry about it, Mathieu.

1063
01:21:15.245 --> 01:21:19.249
Even if Mondain was innocent,
it won't last. We can't help his type.


1064
01:21:19.332 --> 01:21:22.669
- What about justice?
- Let her take care of him.


1065
01:21:22.710 --> 01:21:24.963
Headmaster, wait for me.
Wait for me.


1066
01:21:25.004 --> 01:21:26.965
Are you leaving too?

1067
01:21:27.006 --> 01:21:30.134
I'm getting a lift. I'm spending
the holidays with relatives.


1068
01:21:30.176 --> 01:21:31.970
At my sister's house.

1069
01:21:33.137 --> 01:21:34.973
They have a piano.

1070
01:21:44.607 --> 01:21:46.526
Do you know why Rachin
went to Lyon?


1071
01:21:46.609 --> 01:21:50.488
I think he's supposed to discuss
the balance sheet with the committee.


1072
01:21:51.656 --> 01:21:53.283
- No?
- Yes.


1073
01:21:53.366 --> 01:21:57.120
But he's mostly going to run
after a promotion and a medal.


1074
01:21:58.329 --> 01:22:00.790
Do you think he'll get them?

1075
01:22:00.832 --> 01:22:04.669
He's really smart. He's going
to present an impeccable report


1076
01:22:04.711 --> 01:22:08.047
without saying a word
about all the horrible things.


1077
01:22:08.131 --> 01:22:11.050
He'll even claim the success
of the chorus for himself.


1078
01:22:11.134 --> 01:22:12.135
Success?

1079
01:22:12.218 --> 01:22:14.804
Certainly. I heard them.
They're good.


1080
01:22:15.805 --> 01:22:18.766
Sir, is it true that
Langlois left with the head?


1081
01:22:18.808 --> 01:22:22.145
Yes. Chabert and Carpentier
have taken two weeks' holidays.


1082
01:22:22.186 --> 01:22:24.772
- We're in charge.
- There's no class today?


1083
01:22:26.941 --> 01:22:28.318
No.

1084
01:22:28.359 --> 01:22:30.904
- What are we going to do?
- Take a nap.


1085
01:22:30.987 --> 01:22:33.448
I have a better idea.

1086
01:22:37.869 --> 01:22:39.495
Thank you.

1087
01:22:39.579 --> 01:22:42.665
I don't want to...

1088
01:22:42.749 --> 01:22:45.168
- Your rosette?
- Yes.


1089
01:22:46.920 --> 01:22:49.422
The bird is in the nest, Mr. Rachin.

1090
01:22:50.965 --> 01:22:53.259
I can't thank you enough.

1091
01:22:55.595 --> 01:22:58.514
I'm sorry, Headmaster.
You're wanted on the telephone.


1092
01:23:04.395 --> 01:23:05.980
I'm sorry.

1093
01:23:23.998 --> 01:23:25.375
Headmaster!

1094
01:23:26.376 --> 01:23:29.170
- Do something. My son is up there.
- Let me through.


1095
01:23:29.504 --> 01:23:31.714
The fire had caught under the eaves.

1096
01:23:31.798 --> 01:23:35.677
The dormitories, where the children
had last been seen, were in flames.


1097
01:23:35.760 --> 01:23:37.845
Sixty unfortunate children,

1098
01:23:37.929 --> 01:23:40.098
caught in a snare.

1099
01:23:40.181 --> 01:23:42.850
Rachin saw his promotion
and his rosette


1100
01:23:42.892 --> 01:23:45.061
destroyed before his very eyes.

1101
01:23:45.144 --> 01:23:46.938
But, suddenly...

1102
01:24:36.279 --> 01:24:40.617
After breakfast, we used the door
leading out of the vegetable patch


1103
01:24:40.658 --> 01:24:43.786
to avoid old Marie and the villagers.

1104
01:24:43.870 --> 01:24:45.788
We went to the forest of Lignan.

1105
01:24:45.830 --> 01:24:48.124
For what purpose?

1106
01:24:48.208 --> 01:24:51.711
A treasure hunt.
They were so happy.


1107
01:24:54.964 --> 01:24:59.135
I don't need to tell you
how disappointed I am, Mr. Maxence.


1108
01:24:59.219 --> 01:25:02.138
This was entirely my idea, Headmaster.

1109
01:25:02.222 --> 01:25:05.975
Mr. Maxence never stopped
trying to dissuade me.


1110
01:25:06.059 --> 01:25:07.644
Not very convincing.

1111
01:25:07.685 --> 01:25:11.648
We could also consider the fact
that we saved the children's lives.


1112
01:25:11.731 --> 01:25:15.360
If you hadn't left the school,
it wouldn't have caught fire.


1113
01:25:15.443 --> 01:25:17.946
I don't even know
why I'm listening to you.


1114
01:25:18.029 --> 01:25:23.076
Mr. Maxence, owing to your long years
of service, I'll just suspend you.


1115
01:25:24.160 --> 01:25:26.788
As for you, Mr. 
Mathieu, you're fired.

1116
01:25:26.871 --> 01:25:29.040
For breaking the rules.

1117
01:25:29.082 --> 01:25:31.084
Then you should fire me too.

1118
01:25:31.125 --> 01:25:33.086
You don't get to decide.

1119
01:25:33.169 --> 01:25:37.257
It's nice of you, Mr. Maxence,
but you're needed here.


1120
01:25:37.340 --> 01:25:40.802
Think about the children,
since this gentleman never does.


1121
01:25:44.055 --> 01:25:46.391
I've settled up with you. Here.

1122
01:25:46.432 --> 01:25:49.686
You're leaving right now,
on the 6:00 bus.


1123
01:25:49.727 --> 01:25:52.939
You're allowed no contact
with your former students. None.


1124
01:25:53.022 --> 01:25:55.483
- What?
- Mr. Maxence, see to it.


1125
01:25:55.567 --> 01:25:57.360
Get out.

1126
01:26:01.531 --> 01:26:06.953
Headmaster, before I go,
I'll tell you what I think of you.


1127
01:26:07.036 --> 01:26:10.123
- I already know, Mathieu.
- You're an incompetent,


1128
01:26:10.164 --> 01:26:12.333
- truly evil man.
- What about them?


1129
01:26:12.417 --> 01:26:14.377
They're not here by choice.

1130
01:26:14.460 --> 01:26:16.796
Neither am I.
I never wanted to be a teacher.


1131
01:26:16.838 --> 01:26:19.841
Don't tell me you wanted to come
to that miserable place.


1132
01:26:19.924 --> 01:26:23.052
- You had other ambitions? So did I.
- Don't take it out on them.


1133
01:26:23.094 --> 01:26:25.638
Do you think I like being a warden?

1134
01:26:25.680 --> 01:26:27.640
Someone has to do it.

1135
01:26:27.724 --> 01:26:30.977
Pack up your bags and go to Paris.
Make the Ministry rounds.


1136
01:26:31.060 --> 01:26:33.104
Knock-knock.
"Hello. My name is Mathieu.


1137
01:26:33.187 --> 01:26:35.398
We need real teachers
instead of washouts."


1138
01:26:35.481 --> 01:26:37.984
Fight for the cause
if you believe in it, Mathieu.


1139
01:26:38.067 --> 01:26:40.361
Saint Mathieu.

1140
01:26:40.445 --> 01:26:42.697
You're nothing but a failed musician.

1141
01:26:42.780 --> 01:26:45.867
A prefect. A small prefect.
Small, small, small.


1142
01:26:46.534 --> 01:26:49.329
"What do you do, Mr. Mathieu?"
"I'm a prefect."


1143
01:26:49.370 --> 01:26:51.831
Small. Small. Small.

1144
01:26:52.957 --> 01:26:54.459
You're crazy.

1145
01:26:54.542 --> 01:26:56.127
I'm tired.

1146
01:26:56.211 --> 01:26:57.837
Go to the devil.

1147
01:26:57.921 --> 01:27:00.423
No, I'm leaving him behind.

1148
01:27:13.436 --> 01:27:17.941
I had hoped a few students
would break the rules to say goodbye.


1149
01:27:17.982 --> 01:27:19.984
I saw no one.

1150
01:27:20.068 --> 01:27:23.363
The wisdom of these children
came across as indifference.


1151
01:27:24.030 --> 01:27:26.449
And Morhange...

1152
01:27:26.491 --> 01:27:28.326
Enough.

1153
01:27:47.178 --> 01:27:49.013
"See you soon, Mr. Mathieu."

1154
01:27:49.097 --> 01:27:50.598
"Goodbye, Chrome Dome."

1155
01:27:59.774 --> 01:28:03.069
On the first note, I recognized
Boniface's careful script.


1156
01:28:03.152 --> 01:28:07.323
The spelling mistakes
were Pépinot's, of course.


1157
01:28:07.407 --> 01:28:10.994
This one, filled with music notes,
came from Morhange.


1158
01:28:12.078 --> 01:28:14.247
And this one...

1159
01:28:14.330 --> 01:28:15.832
And that one...

1160
01:28:40.565 --> 01:28:42.525
Be silent! Make them stop!

1161
01:28:42.567 --> 01:28:44.777
The door's locked.

1162
01:28:44.861 --> 01:28:46.529
Open up!

1163
01:28:47.280 --> 01:28:50.742
Right then I felt a sudden burst
ofjoy and optimism.


1164
01:28:50.825 --> 01:28:53.286
I wanted to share it
with the entire world.


1165
01:28:53.369 --> 01:28:55.371
But who would have listened?

1166
01:28:55.496 --> 01:28:58.249
No one even knew I was alive.

1167
01:28:59.167 --> 01:29:02.212
The great artist would soon
give way to the ordinary man.


1168
01:29:03.213 --> 01:29:05.340
I'm Clément Mathieu,

1169
01:29:05.423 --> 01:29:08.343
a failed musician,
an unemployed prefect.


1170
01:29:08.426 --> 01:29:10.511
"I'm Clément Mathieu,

1171
01:29:10.595 --> 01:29:14.432
a failed musician,
an unemployed prefect."


1172
01:29:28.446 --> 01:29:30.698
What happened next?

1173
01:29:30.740 --> 01:29:33.743
He never finished his journal.

1174
01:29:36.287 --> 01:29:39.040
But I can tell you the story.

1175
01:29:41.167 --> 01:29:44.045
Pépinot answered my questions.

1176
01:29:44.087 --> 01:29:49.133
The following day, on the way back,
my childhood caught me by the throat.


1177
01:29:50.343 --> 01:29:54.138
When Mathieu was fired,
my mother took me back home.


1178
01:29:54.222 --> 01:29:57.350
We left for Lyon, where
I was admitted to the Conservatory.


1179
01:29:58.935 --> 01:30:01.396
The engineer tried
to send me to boarding school.


1180
01:30:01.479 --> 01:30:04.357
She refused. He left us.

1181
01:30:05.108 --> 01:30:11.114
Chabert, Langlois and old Maxence
joined forces to expose Rachin's abuse.


1182
01:30:11.155 --> 01:30:15.243
The children were questioned
and Rachin was fired.


1183
01:30:20.290 --> 01:30:24.085
Clément Mathieu gave music lessons
for the rest of his life,


1184
01:30:24.168 --> 01:30:26.671
without courting notoriety.

1185
01:30:26.754 --> 01:30:29.465
Everything he did, he kept for himself.

1186
01:30:30.758 --> 01:30:33.761
For himself? No, not quite.

1187
01:30:33.803 --> 01:30:35.638
Mr. Mathieu.

1188
01:30:38.057 --> 01:30:39.851
Mr. Mathieu.

1189
01:30:42.228 --> 01:30:43.980
Wait a bit.

1190
01:30:46.941 --> 01:30:48.943
Mr. Mathieu.

1191
01:30:54.699 --> 01:30:55.950
What are you doing?

1192
01:30:56.034 --> 01:30:58.620
Can you take me with you?

1193
01:30:58.703 --> 01:31:00.163
Sir.

1194
01:31:00.205 --> 01:31:04.167
I can't do that. You have to go back
to school. They'll punish you.


1195
01:31:04.250 --> 01:31:05.251
Please?

1196
01:31:05.335 --> 01:31:07.545
- Can we go now?
- Coming.


1197
01:31:07.629 --> 01:31:10.798
It's forbidden.
I can't take you with me.


1198
01:31:10.882 --> 01:31:12.550
Go back.

1199
01:31:12.634 --> 01:31:14.302
Go on.

1200
01:31:14.636 --> 01:31:16.304
Go on.

1201
01:31:41.871 --> 01:31:44.457
Pépinot had been right all along.

1202
01:31:44.541 --> 01:31:47.335
Mathieu was fired on a Saturday.